threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an ARM-based malware, likely a botnet agent. It performs extensive enumeration of running processes by inspecting the `/proc` filesystem (e.g., `/proc/[pid]/exe`, `/proc/[pid]/cmdline`, `/proc/net/tcp`). This is characteristic of malware attempting to identify and kill competing processes or security software. The binary modifies its own OOM (Out Of Memory) score via `/proc/self/oom_score_adj` and `/proc/self/oom_adj` to ensure its persistence. It also prepares to execute shell commands using `/bin/sh`, a common backdoor behavior.
